Do not run lupdate during the build.

translations/CMakeLists.txt regenerates glabels_C.ts and templates_C.ts with
lupdate on every build.  That is a maintainer task, not something a packaging
build needs: both .ts files are committed upstream, and lrelease alone is
enough to produce the .qm files that get installed.

It also breaks the build here.  Qt6's lupdate is the clang-based parser and
needs libclang.dll, which is not part of the qttools archive that aqtinstall
fetches, so lupdate.exe dies with STATUS_DLL_NOT_FOUND (0xC0000135) and
MSBuild reports a bare error MSB8066.

Switching the two C-locale files to qt6_add_translation drops lupdate (and the
XmlStrings string-extraction step that only fed it) from the build.  The other
84 languages already went through qt6_add_translation.

Removable once upstream stops running lupdate as part of the default build.

diff --git a/translations/CMakeLists.txt b/translations/CMakeLists.txt
index d5fe9f1..6225fdf 100644
--- a/translations/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/translations/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -20,19 +20,13 @@ expand_linguas (GLABELS_TS_FILES "LINGUAS" "glabels")
 expand_linguas (TEMPLATES_TS_FILES "LINGUAS" "templates")
 
 #
-# Update strings in C-locale translation files (lupdate+lrelease)
+# Compile the C-locale translation files (lrelease only)
 #
-qt6_create_translation (glabels_C_qm_file
-  ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/glabels
-  ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/model
-  ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/backends
+qt6_add_translation (glabels_C_qm_file
   glabels_C.ts
-  OPTIONS -no-obsolete -locations none
 )
-qt6_create_translation (templates_C_qm_file
-  ${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/template-strings.hpp
+qt6_add_translation (templates_C_qm_file
   templates_C.ts
-  OPTIONS -no-obsolete -locations none
 )
 
 #
